Description. Lectotype , male. Length. Pronotum + elytra: 5.3 mm . Color. Antenna, tarsi and rostrum ferruginous; head, prothorax and legs ferruginous to black; elytra and remaining ventral surface dark red. Habitus elongate-subovate, in dorsal view slightly constricted between pronotum and elytra (
Fig. 6
); profile dorsally constricted between pronotum and elytron (
Fig. 15
).

Selected female specimen. Same as holotype except: Rostrum 6.50 X longer than wide. Prothorax 1.06 X longer than wide. Elytra as long as wide; apex less extended, slightly more slender. Metafemur without concavity basal to stridulatory patch, posteroventral ridges slightly protruding. Terminalia. Hemisternites of ovipositor 10.75 X longer than wide. Tergite VII (
Fig. 60
) 2.23 X longer than wide. Tergite VIII (
Fig. 59
) 1.93 X longer than wide. Bursal sclerite (
Fig. 65
) at insertion of spermathecal duct weakly sclerotized.
